      "writtenOn": "2021-04-03T06:13:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e to be clear: there is a bug currently that if there is a line that exceeds scanner buffer size (which defaults to 64KB), then scan.Err() will return bufio.ErrBufferFull,\n\nI should fix this error by:\n1. call sc.Buffer(buf, b.maxTokenSize) to make sure if a line exceeds b.maxTokenSize, scanner will use the buf without allocation (https://go.googlesource.com/go/+/go1.16.2/src/bufio/scan.go#261).\n\n2. the customized Split handles the case that scanner scan a chunk of data without linebreak at https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/infra/luci/luci-go/+/2801097/12/resultdb/internal/services/bqexporter/text_artifact_row.go#137.",
      "parentUuid": "0db2e22c_4e7b69a5",
